==English==

===Adjective===
'''leaden'''
#{{dated}} made of [[lead]]
# as [[heavy]] as lead
# slow moving; [[sluggish]]
# lacking [[vitality]]; [[languid]]
# [[depressed]] or [[spiritless]]
# the [[colour]] of lead; dull [[grey]]; [[overcast]] (of weather)

===Quotations===
#*'''1999:''' "It was at the end of February..., when the world was cold..., when icy rains fell from the '''leaden''' skies in continual drizzling showers."  &mdash; ''Stardust'', Neil Gaiman, page 31 (2001 Perennial paperback edition).